####################################################
1) Required Libraries

$ apt-get install libboost-all-dev libboost-dev liblog4cxx10-dev

####################################################
2) Compiling Binaries

$ cd src/
$ make all

####################################################
3) Run Binaries

The make file creates two binaries in SVN/bin: the OpenMSC and a receiver dummy. First copy the example configuration files to the SVN/bin directory:
$ cd ../bin
$ cp ../doc/example/openmsc.msc .
$ cp ../doc/example/openmsc.cfg .

If both binaries are located on the same machine just invoke:

$ ./receiverDummy 8000

in one terminal and 

$ ./openmsc -i 127.0.0.1 -p 8000

in another one.
